Where is it? Q. So, in the very -- I'm looking in the first page of Defendant's Exhibit J-3 in the top header, the very first top of the document under applicant information, do you see about five lines down underneath the names of your siblings, the line there? A. Yes. Yes. Sorry. Q. In your application, did you have to list your height and weight? A. Yes. Q. And how tall were you when you were going to summer camp that summer? A. Five-two. Q. How many pounds did you weigh? A. 90. Q. What grade were you in? A. Seventh grade. Q. I want to ask you about the next year you went to Interlochen. If you could turn to -- MS. MOE: I'd ask for permission for the jurors to turn to Defendant's Exhibit J-4 which is in evidence under seal. THE COURT: Without objection, you may. MS. MENNINGER: Yes, your Honor.
